{"title_page": "Albert Ganado", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=July 2019}}\n\n'''Albert Ganado''' [[National Order of Merit (Malta)|MOM]] (born 9 March 1924) is a Maltese lawyer and historian.<ref>[https://bdlbooks.com/authors/albert-ganado/ Albert Ganado.] BDL Books. Retrieved 6 June 2019.</ref> He is a past president of the [[Malta Historical Society]]<ref>[https://www.britannica.com/contributor/Albert-Ganado/6605 Albert Ganado.] britannica.com Retrieved 6 June 2019.</ref> and the founder and president of the [[Malta Map Society]].<ref>[https://maltamapsociety.mt/pascal-brun-from-castellar-visits-dr-albert-ganado/ Pascal Brun from Castellar visits Dr Albert Ganado.] Joseph Schir\u00f2, Malta Map Society, 17 April 2019. Retrieved 6 June 2019.</ref>\n\n==Selected publications==\n* ''Malta in British and French Caricature 1798 \u2013 1815''. Said International, 1989. (With Joseph C. Sammut) {{ISBN|1871684455}}\n* ''A Study in Depth of 143 Maps Representing the Great Siege of Malta of 1565''. Publishers Enterprise Group, 1994. (With [[Maurice Agius-Vadala]]) {{ISBN|9990900507}}\n* ''Palace of the Grand Masters in Valletta''. Fondazzjoni Patrimonju Malti, 2001. {{ISBN|9993210129}}\n* ''Miniature Maps of Malta''. Midsea Books, 2009. {{ISBN|978-9993272724}}\n* ''German Malta Maps''. BDL Publishing, 2011. (With [[Joseph Schir\u00f2]]) {{ISBN|978-9995733209}} \n* ''The Brocktorff Mapmakers''. BDL Publishing, 2012. (With Joseph Schir\u00f2 & [[Claude Micallef Attard]]) {{ISBN|978-9995733735}}\n* ''Malta in World War II: Contemporary Watercolours by Alfred Gerada''. Midsea Books, [2018]. {{ISBN|9789993276166}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* ''Liber amicorum: Essays on art, history, cartography, and bibliography in honour of Dr. Albert Ganado''. University of Malta, 1994. {{ISBN|9990946027}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ganado, Albert}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1924 births]]\n[[Category:Historians of cartography]]\n[[Category:Maltese historians]]\n[[Category:Maltese lawyers]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the National Order of Merit (Malta)]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Malta]]\n\n\n{{Malta-bio-stub}}\n{{historian-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=July 2019}}\n\n'''Albert Ganado''' [[National Order of Merit (Malta)|MOM]] (born 9 March 1924) is a Maltese lawyer and historian.<ref>[https://bdlbooks.com/authors/albert-ganado/ Albert Ganado.] BDL Books. Retrieved 6 June 2019.</ref> He is a past president of the [[Malta Historical Society]]<ref>[https://www.britannica.com/contributor/Albert-Ganado/6605 Albert Ganado.] britannica.com Retrieved 6 June 2019.</ref> and the founder and president of the [[Malta Map Society]].<ref>[https://maltamapsociety.mt/pascal-brun-from-castellar-visits-dr-albert-ganado/ Pascal Brun from Castellar visits Dr Albert Ganado.] Joseph Schir\u00f2, Malta Map Society, 17 April 2019. Retrieved 6 June 2019.</ref>\n\n==Selected publications==\n* ''Malta in British and French Caricature 1798 \u2013 1815''. Said International, 1989. (With Joseph C. Sammut) {{ISBN|1871684455}}\n* ''A Study in Depth of 143 Maps Representing the Great Siege of Malta of 1565''. Publishers Enterprise Group, 1994. (With [[Maurice Agius-Vadala]]) {{ISBN|9990900507}}\n* ''Palace of the Grand Masters in Valletta''. Fondazzjoni Patrimonju Malti, 2001. {{ISBN|9993210129}}\n* ''Miniature Maps of Malta''. Midsea Books, 2009. {{ISBN|978-9993272724}}\n* ''German Malta Maps''. BDL Publishing, 2011. (With [[Joseph Schir\u00f2]]) {{ISBN|978-9995733209}} \n* ''The Brocktorff Mapmakers''. BDL Publishing, 2012. (With Joseph Schir\u00f2 & [[Claude Micallef Attard]]) {{ISBN|978-9995733735}}\n* ''Malta in World War II: Contemporary Watercolours by Alfred Gerada''. Midsea Books, [2018]. {{ISBN|9789993276166}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* ''Liber amicorum: Essays on art, history, cartography, and bibliography in honour of Dr. Albert Ganado''. University of Malta, 1994. 